VSangeetha Ksheera Sagaram featured violin solo by Ramaraju Dinakar.Dinakar is an A-grade artiste and has decent experience of accompanying many seniorvidwansin the field. Having a good knowledge of music and also a fine technique on the violin, he began his recital with ThodiVarnamwhich sounded very apt. Mayamalava Gowla was briefly essayed for Thyagaraja&#8217;sTulasidalamulachewith crispswaram. Thepathantharacould have been better. Devaghandhari was taken next and Dinakar tookKsheera Sagara Shaina, a masterpiece of Thyagaraja and displayed with completeraga bhavamwhich was a noteworthy presentation.Kalaharana melarawas the next item which was played in Dhuritha Kala. Chandra Jyothi was taken for a detailed expansion and theragamwas played in a soothing way.Bagayanayyawith Sarvalaghuswaramwas well played by the artiste.Arthanareeswaram,a Shivan composition was played with good feel.Sankarabharanamwas the main attraction of the day. Dinaker did his best in theragampart and some important classicalsangathiswere just missing from the bow. Thyagaraja&#8217;sEnduku peddalavalewas thekrithiandswaramwith matchyprastharam.The concert was enhanced to new heights by the soothing and melodious following by Kapa Srinivas on the mridangam. Histanialong with Janardhan on the ghatam in Aditalamfor four Aksharas Eddupu was effective. Finally Dinakar concluded with the famous Lalgudi&#8217;sthillanain theragamMohanakalyanai.On the whole Dinakar displayed a melodious violin solo recital showing signs of maturity.
